{
  "texts": [
    "In detail, they produce pseudo BoW from the predictive word probability of BERT.",
    "Then their NTM reconstructs both the real and pseudo BoW.",
    "Bianchi et al (2021b); Mueller and Dredze (2021) employ multilingual BERT to infer cross-lingual doc-topic distributions for zeroshot learning but they cannot discover aligned cross-lingual topics.",
    "As a self-supervised learning fashion, contrastive learning has been employed to facilitate NTMs.",
    "The idea of contrastive learning is to measure the similarity relations among sample pairs in a representation space (Van den Oord et al 2018)."
  ]
}